All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Actioneer
    Defines the actioneer crew member, Actioneer can do 3 actions instead of the usual 2
    AlienPirates
    Defines one of the random events, Alien pirates can steal one of the player's consumables
    AsteroidBelt
    Defines one of the random events, Asteroid belt can cause damage to the spaceship whenever the crew goes to another planet
    Brownie
    Defines Food - Brownie, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Builder
    Defines the builder crew member, Builder can repair the spaceship faster
    CommandCenter
    Defines window where the game is being played, the player can see the crew status, commit actions, view spaceship status, and visit outpost
    Consumable
    Defines Abstract class for all the consumables in the game
    Crew
    Defines a crew object.
    CrewMember
    Defines the crew member for the crew.
    CrewMemberNotFoundException
    Exception that is thrown when attempting to delete an non existent crew member
    DarkSlider
    Defines a custom slider for the setup screen
    Dumplings
    Defines Food - Dumplings, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Explorer
    Defines a explorer crew member, explorer has better chances of finding an item compared to other crew members
    FinalScreen
    Defines window showing the final score when the game has ended
    Food
    Defines Abstract class for all the foods in the game
    FriedRice
    Defines Food - FriedRice, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Game
    Defines the command line implementation for the game
    GameEngine
    Defines the game environment that keeps track of all the components in the game.
    GameGUI
    Defines GUI Manager that handles which window to open/close next
    Hotbot
    Defines Food - Hotbot, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Hungus
    Defines a Hungus crew member, Hungus benefits more from eating and gets hungry slower compared to other crew members
    InsufficientActionException
    Exception that is thrown when an unit attempts to do some action when they are out of actions
    InsufficientFundException
    Exception that is thrown when there are not enough money to purchase something from the outpost
    InsufficientItemInStock
    Exception that is thrown when there are not enough items in the stock
    Medic
    Defines a Medic crew member, Medic receives less damage compared to other crew members
    MedicalSupply
    Defines Abstract class for all the medical supplies in the game
    ModernTab
    Defines a smart looking tab that is implemented in the Command Center window
    Outpost
    Defines shop where player can buy food and medical supply for the crew
    PickledPlum
    Defines Medical Supply - PickledPlum, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Planet
    Defines the planet where crew can travel to, some of the planets have ship pieces
    PolyJuice
    Defines Medical Supply - PolyJuice, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    RandomEvents
    Defines an interface that every random events have to implement.
    SetupScreen
    Defines window that handles the initial setup of crew member, game length and spaceship
    ShoppingCart
    Defines the shopping cart of the player, keeps track of items and prices
    Sleeper
    Defines a Sleeper crew member, Sleeper benefits more from sleeping compared to other crew members
    SpaceCake
    Defines Food - SpaceCake, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    SpacePlague
    Defines one of the random events, Space Plague causes health of the crew members to reduce every day until they consumed an item that cures space plague
    Spaceship
    Defines a spaceship, the crew member uses a spaceship to get from planet to planet.
    StrandeD
    Defines the first window that shows the title, start and load button
    TikkaMasala
    Defines Food - TikkaMasala, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
    Unit
    Defines a unit.
    Utils
    Defines utilities that are used to make the game prettier, mostly used by the command line application
    Vaccine
    Defines Medical Supply - Vaccine, can be consumed to increase health and decrease hunger
